# Gitavale — Cursor Rules

## Project
Next.js 14 SaaS that turns GitHub repos into LLM-ready digests.
- App dir: `/app` (Next.js App Router)
- DB: Prisma + PostgreSQL — `prisma/schema.prisma`
- Auth: NextAuth.js — `lib/auth.ts`
- Payments: Polar.sh — `lib/polar.ts`, `app/api/checkout/route.ts`
- API Keys: `lib/apiAuth.ts` (SHA-256 Bearer tokens prefixed `gta_`)
- CLI: Python — `cli-anything-gitavale/`

## Skills
Read `.agents/skills/gitavale/SKILL.md` for full API docs, schema, and env vars.

## Key Conventions
- All new API routes go in `app/api/`
- Use `getServerSession(authOptions)` for auth in server components
- New Prisma fields: cast with `as any` locally until `prisma generate` runs on deploy
- Unstyled components use utility classes from `globals.css` (glass-panel, btn-primary, etc.)
- Push to GitHub → Vercel auto-deploys (postinstall runs `prisma db push`)
